---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="PYRS Docs | Getting Started"
	description="Getting started guide for PYRS runtime usage and first execution flow."
	pageTitle="Getting Started"
>
	<section class="intro">
		<p>
			PYRS is a Python interpreter in Rust targeting CPython 3.14 compatibility. This page covers
			the fastest way to install, verify, and start running code.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Prerequisites</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Rust stable toolchain (`rustup`, `cargo`)</li>
			<li>Git</li>
			<li>macOS or Linux</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Install and Verify</h2>
		<p>Install the latest `pyrs` directly from GitHub and verify your binary is available.</p>
		<pre><code>cargo install --locked --git https://github.com/BlueBlazin/pyrs --bin pyrs
pyrs --version</code></pre>
		<p>For all install methods (Cargo source build, Docker, nightly archives), see the Installation page.</p>
		<p><a class="doc-link" href="/docs/install/">Open Installation Guide</a></p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Run Python</h2>
		<p>Start with REPL, inline command mode, and source-file execution.</p>
		<pre><code>pyrs
pyrs -c "import sys; print(sys.version)"
pyrs path/to/script.py</code></pre>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Next Steps</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Review <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/reference/">CLI and Environment Reference</a>.</li>
			<li>Use <code>pyrs --help</code> to inspect runtime options directly from the binary.</li>
			<li>Track release and compatibility progress in the project repository.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
	.intro p {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	section + section {
		margin-top: 1.35rem;
	}

	.doc-link {
		color: #9fb5e6;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(159, 181, 230, 0.45);
	}

	.doc-link:hover {
		color: #bed0f0;
		border-bottom-color: rgba(190, 208, 240, 0.75);
	}
</style>
